SubscriptionGuard.source is a STRONG Arc<dyn DepNode> (subscription.rs:12). sample_on (source.rs:341-355) captures a STRONG cell clone in the notifier closure, then does cell.own(guard):

  CellInner -> owned(guard) -> Arc<Source> -> subscribers -> closure -> Arc<CellInner>

Neither side is ever freed. CellInner::drop never runs, so (a) the cell leaks, (b) it never deregisters from the trace registry, inflating any live-cell census, and (c) the closure KEEPS SAMPLING on every notifier tick forever - a CPU leak as well as a memory one. Per-orphaned-cell, so it accumulates with cell churn rather than with time.

FIX SHAPE (design call is hyphae's): capture a Weak/downgraded handle in the subscriber closure and upgrade inside (dropping the tick if upgrade fails), or make the guard hold a Weak source. Note the guard's strong source is load-bearing for own()/add_height_dependent, so weakening it needs care.

Consumers reproduce the same shape by hand (rship lv-df48): rship libs/sync/src/clock.rs:64-76 and libs/sync/src/value_runner.rs:279-289 - a destroyed sync value's sampled cell + its ValueRunner stay alive and keep ticking.

